title: Sting of Death
description:
STING OF DEATH (1966)
Directed by William Grefe

Released with the more famous Death Curse of Tartu, this was a rare obscurity until Something Weird Video released it on DVD in the early 21st century. That is progress not envisioned by the creators of The Jetsons . . . 

Young adults party in south Florida, and the deformed man whom they mock devises a means of transforming himself into a jellyfish. Some of the most ridiculous monster effects ever filmed, combined with vivid, colorful photography and some very beautiful, terrorized young women, resulting in one of the most entertaining "bad films" imaginable.

Starring Joe Morrison, Valerie Hawkins, and John Vella as Egon, the half-man, half-jellyfish!

Neil Sedaka provides the bouncy theme song "Do the Jellyfish!" You can't miss it.
